\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 >Electricity - You were walking home one day when the sound of thunder rumbled above you. Not the most welcome sound, as you still had a ways to go, and didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t have anything to keep you dry. You felt the small hairs on the back of your neck raise and you knew instantly what was about to happen. Before you had a chance to think, the lightning hit you and\u8230\'85 nothing. You were fine. You could still feel it, like a pulse, coarsing through you - but you were still conscious, and still breathing. You took a step forward and felt suddenly dizzy. You reached out to stabilize yourself, when the electricity you could feel inside you suddenly pulsed out of your hand. You thought, for a moment, that you were hallucinating, that maybe the lightning had done some damage, and maybe you weren\u8217\'92t actually conscious. So you tried to make it happen again, on purpose this time - and it did. }}